SUMMARY:Art in Action: Spectacular Seed Bombs
DESCRIPTION:Art in Action in Davis: Spectacular Seed Bombs \nSaturday\, May 30\, 1-3 PM \n$5 Members\, $10 Non-Members (per person\, all materials included) \nLearn about the ancient Japanese practice of seed bombs! Using air-dry clay and native wildflower seeds\, make seed bombs that you can later plant outdoors or in a garden. Decorate your seed bombs with dried petals and stamps\, and design and illustrate a plant care card to help you take care of the wildflowers you plant. \n  \nHow it works: \nArt in Action engages kids in art projects that are fun\, creative\, and collaborative with their family members. This is a drop-in program for ages 5-12. No registration in advance is required\, but space and supplies are limited to the first 25 participants and are available on a first come\, first served basis.  \n  \nWhen you arrive\, pay with cash or card at the front desk. A parent or adult caregiver is required to stay\, but only has to pay for the project for themselves if they are also doing art. Stay as long or as short as you like over the two hour period.  \n  \nBecome a Member starting at $70/year and save! If you join the Pence Gallery when you attend this workshop\, you can enjoy Member pricing for Art in Action\, plus receive a $5 gift certificate to our gift shop as a thank you. Membership supports art for all ages and makes creative moments like this possible—jump in and be part of it. \n  \nWe have a different Art in Action family workshop every month! Learn more at https://pencegallery.org/art-in-action/. \n  \nThis unique monthly program is generously sponsored and made possible by Mary Stephens DeWall and Les DeWall.
URL:https://visityolo.com/event/art-in-action-spectacular-seed-bombs/
LOCATION:Pence Gallery\, 212 D Street\, Davis\, CA 95616
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://visityolo.com/wp-content/uploads/Art-in-Action-logo-copy.jpeg
ORGANIZER;CN="Pence Gallery":MAILTO:pencesocialmedia@gmail.com
END:VEVENT
